The paper deals with the problem of computing personalized reserve prices in auctions, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The paper also presents an LP formulation and a rounding procedure, which are techniques commonly used in optimization and algorithms research (cs.DS). The problem of computing personalized reserve prices is also relevant in the context of machine learning and recommendation systems (cs.AI). The goal of the problem is to maximize revenue, which is a topic in economics and mechanism design (cs.EC). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of an LP formulation, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
